    "cycleDescription": "North Italy Representative Farms - embodying the average dairy farms in Northern Italy present in the Po plain that make milk for Grana Padano cheese production. The cattle feed was based on silage feed (primarily corn silage), forage, protein ingredients (such as soybean meal), corn cereals, alfalfa, and compound feed. In this farm system, cattle were not allowed to graze.",
